  "action_input": "{ \"prompt\": \"A professional component library diagram for a water management system. The layout is clean and organized into three distinct color-coded categories on a light gray background. Category 1: 'Physical Components' (Blue #5B9BD5) featuring icons for Reservoir, River, Gate, Pump Station, Pipeline, and Valve. Category 2: 'Hydrological Components' (Orange #ED7D31) featuring icons for Rainfall, Evaporation, Runoff Generation, Flow Routing, and Groundwater. Category 3: 'Model Components' (Green #70AD47) featuring icons for Hydrodynamics, Water Quality, Ecology, and Economics. Style is a modern business infographic with grouped boxes and simple, minimalist icons. Professional typography, high resolution, suitable for a corporate presentation.\", \"size\": \"1024x1024\" }",
  "thought": "I will generate a professional infographic that follows the specific color coding and categorization requested. Since the user requested a specific resolution (1400x1000), I will aim for a balanced layout that fits well within the standard DALL-E square or wide output, ensuring the text and icons are clear and legible for a presentation."
